The paper deals with the problem of counting independent sets in a graph, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity and graph theory. The paper uses a combination of two well-known methods, "Divide and Conquer" and "Measure and Conquer", and introduces a new concept of "Divide, Measure and Conquer" method. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CG (Computational Geometry).
